This paper discusses the use of signal processing techniques for location awareness in wireless networks, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques such as Gaussian process regression, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges and applications of the proposed solution, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
